m_json", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "browse_pypi", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "pymodaq_version", "type": {"name": "Version", "xref": {"fqname": "packaging.version.Version", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "print_method", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["get PyMoDAQ plugins\n\nParameters\n----------\nfrom_json: bool\n    if True get the plugins list and source files from the json data file (deprecated) else from the pypi server\nbrowse_pypi: bool\n    if from_json is False:\n        if True get the list of plugins name from the https://pypi.org/simple/ website, then get the sources from\n        the pypiserver\n        if False, get the list of plugins name from the json data, then fetch the source from the pypi server\npymodaq_version: Version\n    the current version of PyMoDAQ\nprint_method: Callable\n    a callable accepting string\nReturns\n-------\nplugins_available: list of available plugins for installation\nplugins_installed: list of already installed plugins\nplugins_update: list of plugins with existing update"]}, {"name": "pymodaq_plugin_manager.validate.post_error", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pymodaq_plugin_manager.validate.extract_authors_from_description", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "description", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["returns the authors as a list from the plugin package description (it should follow the template structure)\n\nParameters\n----------\ndescription: (str)\n\nReturns\n-------\nlist of string"]}, {"name": "pymodaq_plugin_manager.validate.capitalize", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "string", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "Nfirst", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns same string but with first Nfirst letters uppe